What are Nail Clippers?
Nail clippers are essential hand tools used for trimming fingernails, toenails, and hangnails. These devices are primarily manufactured from stainless steel, though variants made from plastic and aluminum are also commercially available. The market includes several product types such as lever-type clippers, nipper clippers, and scissor clippers. Lever-type clippers, including the common compound lever and plier designs, dominate the market due to their ease of use and efficient mechanical advantage. The market's expansion is further supported by growing applications in pet care, adding a new dimension to this established consumer goods category.
